Job Description:
At EY, we’re all in to shape your future with confidence.
We’ll help you succeed in a globally connected powerhouse of diverse teams and take your career wherever you want it to go.
Join EY and help to build a better working world.

The opportunity
The opportunity in tax career with focus on Transfer Pricing (TP)
The Government and the Vietnamese tax authorities are more and more focus on Transfer Pricing compliance of taxpayers. Accordingly, you will be a part of clients serving team to support our client in managing a good transfer pricing compliance position, excellent transfer pricing design and strategy set up. You will also have chance to work with the best talented people of EY and our commitment to offer you great career path with the experience that lasts a lifetime.
Within EY Vietnam’s Transfer Pricing practice, we are currently seeking individuals to participate in an exciting multiple client engagement teams and other related activities based in Hanoi office.

Major responsibilities
1. Have a solid understanding of transfer pricing concepts, relevant transfer pricing and tax regulations and effectively apply the knowledge to client situations;
2. Prepare and suggest quality and practical approaches by understanding client’s data, supply chain and business situation under the guidance of the managers;
3. Assist in developing and delivering quality transfer pricing reports, benchmark studies and related work products;
4. Assist in defending our clients during transfer pricing audits and applying APAs;
5. Participate and contribute in achieving team goals

A. To handle Freight Forwarding (Sea/Air Export/Import)
B. To handle Contract Logistics Jobs (Customs Clearance, Warehouse, Bonded Warehouse, Free House Delivery…), check H/S code.
C. Other tasks requested by manager
* Detailed job for Freight Forwarding:
Import:
• Receive document from oversea;
• Submit e-manifest to customs;
• Receive A/N from Airline, Carrier then issue A/N, D/N to customer;
• Make payment to Carrier;
• Pick up D/O from Carrier (if any);
• Receive payment from customer and release D/O to customer;
• To handle customs clearance and import handling service based on trade term;
• Other tasks requested by manager
Export:
• Receive booking order from customer;
• Get booking confirmation from carrier and release to customer;
• Do export customs clearance and pick up for export based on trade term;
• Issue document (BL, Cargo manifest, D/N) to customer, etc…;
• Submit S/I, file AFR, AMS (if any);
• Check D/N from carrier and make payment to carrier;
• Other tasks requested by manager
* * Detailed job for Contract Logistics:
• Receive document from customer, do customs clearance and delivery as customer’s request.
• Check HS code and consult to customer (if needed);
• Other tasks requested by manager
• Warehouse/Bonded Warehouse: same as details job for import + arrange shipment to BWH-IN and BWH-OUT; inventory check.

